snippet.textDisplay: I'm a little confused with this video. They seem to be encouraging the use of PIA (Private Internet Access), just after the talk about how governments want to break Encryption etc. Isn't PIA under jurisdiction of 5 eyes? Rendering that VPN mute? I know, no logs are supposedly kept but what if the government wanted to force them to give them access to everyones connection in realtime to see what they are doing with a backdoor to the encryption or something? I understand there's not really a way to gurantee 100% security from this type of stuff, but I thought it would make sense to use a VPN outside of these jurisdictions such as ExpressVPN, NordVPN etc.
snippet.textOriginal: I'm a little confused with this video. They seem to be encouraging the use of PIA (Private Internet Access), just after the talk about how governments want to break Encryption etc. Isn't PIA under jurisdiction of 5 eyes? Rendering that VPN mute? I know, no logs are supposedly kept but what if the government wanted to force them to give them access to everyones connection in realtime to see what they are doing with a backdoor to the encryption or something? I understand there's not really a way to gurantee 100% security from this type of stuff, but I thought it would make sense to use a VPN outside of these jurisdictions such as ExpressVPN, NordVPN etc.
